In a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki announced that President Biden will be visiting North Carolina Agricultural and Technical State University to tour their new Engineering Research & Innovation Complex. Psaki highlighted the administration's investments in historically black colleges and universities (HBCUs) and the importance of the Bipartisan Innovation Act in creating jobs and supporting domestic manufacturing. She also mentioned Vice President Kamala Harris's meeting on reducing maternal mortality and morbidity and provided updates on judicial nominees and the situation in Ukraine. Psaki addressed questions about the President's use of the term "genocide" to describe the situation in Ukraine, potential enhanced sanctions on Russia, and the recent arrival of migrants in Washington, D.C. She also discussed inflation, the possibility of canceling student debt, and the G20 summit.